props.name: ariaLabel
props.docs: Specifies the label to use for accessibility. Defaults to the icon name.

props.name: flipRtl
props.docs: Specifies whether the icon should horizontally flip when `dir` is `"rtl"`.

props.name: icon
props.docs:
A combination of both `name` and `src`. If a `src` url is detected
it will set the `src` property. Otherwise it assumes it's a built-in named
SVG and set the `name` property.

props.name: ios
props.docs: Specifies which icon to use on `ios` mode.

props.name: lazy
props.docs:
If enabled, stellar-icon will be loaded lazily when it's visible in the viewport.
Default, `false`.

props.name: md
props.docs: Specifies which icon to use on `md` mode.

props.name: mode
props.docs: The mode determines which platform styles to use.

props.name: name
props.docs: Specifies which icon to use from the built-in set of icons.

props.name: size
props.docs:

Available options are: `"small"` and `"large"`.

props.name: src

components.readme:
# ion-slide

The Slide component is a child component of [Slides](../Slides). The template
should be written as `ion-slide`. Any slide content should be written
in this component and it should be used in conjunction with [Slides](../Slides).

See the [Slides API Docs](../Slides) for more usage information.

# stellar-slides

The Slides component is a multi-section container. Each section can be swiped
or dragged between. It contains any number of [Slide](../Slide) components.
